# How_to_Git
Introduction to Github

This repository has the goal to educate the user on how to properly use the github platform. 
By following the below, provided steps, you can set up the stepping stone for expaning your 
knoweldge. Each and evey command is explained in details, including some screenshot for better
interface visualization. 

## Create a repository: 

### Step 1

* First you need to navigate to the github platform console.
* On the Upper-right corner, you see a button, that says new.
* Click on the button and you will be redirected to a new web page so you can modify your repository.


![Screenshot 2023-10-10 at 17 01 57](https://github.com/AlexMitev21/How_to_Git/assets/143809569/79343029-c4e9-4876-980b-e12ef24c9234)

&nbsp;

### Step 2

* Now you have to name the repository and configure it.
* Recomened to make your repository <i>Private</i>
* Do not choose the option to <i>" Add a README file </i>, 
  because you will be creating that later on. 
* Do not chose any license from the dropdown menu. 
* Click <i>Create repository</i>


![Screenshot 2023-10-10 at 17 02 18](https://github.com/AlexMitev21/How_to_Git/assets/143809569/7eaea0ef-d3a9-4501-8134-31dac224fcda)
